        <page n="01" image="va.au.ss.1857.04.29.01">
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>The Oringinal Dred Scott</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>He does not take on airs, however, but laughs heartily when talking of "de
                    fuss dey made dar in Washington 'bout de ole nigger."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Biography of Dred Scott, "the distinguished colored individual who has made
                    such a noise in the world." Says Scott does not seem discouraged by outcome of
                    case. Commends him for not running away to freedom.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>7</column>
